  10 Oct 2009; Tristan Heaven <nyhm@gentoo.org>
  ut2004-bonuspack-mega-1-r2.ebuild:
  EAPI=2; remove dedicated and opengl USE flags; let games-mods.eclass
  handle install

  28 Jul 2008; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Removing myself from metadata.xml since I am retiring from the project.

  10 Jan 2007; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  -ut2004-bonuspack-mega-1-r1.ebuild, ut2004-bonuspack-mega-1-r2.ebuild:
  Stable on amd64/x86 and removing older versions.

*ut2004-bonuspack-mega-1-r2 (07 Nov 2006)

  07 Nov 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  +ut2004-bonuspack-mega-1-r2.ebuild:
  Added new revision for testing which uses the brand-spankin-new
  games-mods.eclass to reduce ebuild code.

  26 Sep 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  ut2004-bonuspack-mega-1-r1.ebuild:
  Remove dependency on ut2004 since this causes circular dependencies. Closing
  bug #149024.

  11 Apr 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  ut2004-bonuspack-mega-1-r1.ebuild:
  Marking stable on amd64/x86 to bring in new Mega bonuspack and to close bug
  #129373.

  31 Mar 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  ut2004-bonuspack-mega-1-r1.ebuild:
  Changed nomirror to mirror and nostrip to strip.

  20 Mar 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  -ut2004-bonuspack-mega-1.ebuild, ut2004-bonuspack-mega-1-r1.ebuild:
  Changed DESCRIPTION to remove redundant 'pack' and cleaning up older ebuilds.

  17 Mar 2006; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org>
  +ut2004-bonuspack-mega-1-r1.ebuild:
  Added a new revision from Paul Bredbury <brebs@sent.com> and closing bug
  #123202, bug #116528, and bug #126538.

